FT  03 OCT 92 / VAT decision
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HOLDING COMPANIES will no longer be able to recover value added tax in
carrying out their basic functions, Customs &amp; Excise said yesterday.
Activities such as the acquisition of shares and subsidiaries, mounting or
defending against takeovers and receiving dividends will cease to be
tax-deductible from March 1 next year.
