<HEADLINE>
FT  03 OCT 92 / Markets: At a Glance - Unit trust sales improve
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Unit trust business recovered slightly in August, before the sterling
crisis, with a net inflow of Pounds 56m following net outflows in June and
July. The Unit Trust Association interpreted the rise as showing that
private investors' confidence in the UK stock market had recovered. The net
inflow to UK Growth funds from private investors was Pounds 73m, while
Pounds 59m came from institutions. Other UK sectors also recorded strong
inflows.
