<HEADLINE>
FT  02 OCT 92 / Survey of Software at Work - Autumn 1992 (34): CCN Marketing
 -Supplier Profile
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CCN Marketing was founded in the UK in 1989 and is part of the CCN Group.
Turnover: Pounds 61.4m in 1990/91 and Pounds 66.8m in 1991/92. The company
has about 1,000 employees in the UK.
Specialist vertical markets: retailing, financial, media and leisure, but
CCN's services can apply to consumer markets in any sector.
Software products: include Mosaic Systems and a range of PC and mainframe
products for database marketing; these are called Oasis, Relations, and
Tactics. Mosaic provides personal computer market analysis software for
mapping and reporting on catchment areas, geographical regions, media
regions and customer files. They are used for branch development, network
evaluation, merchandise planning and planning of promotional activity.
Hardware and operating systems: PC to mainframe.
Services cover consultancy, system development training and maintenance.
User comments: 'Expertise of bureau staff . . . regular data and technology
updates.'
