an integrated system called Uni 2000, all for mainframe computers; Open Door
for the Unix operating system; PS 2000 for personal computers.
Hardware: IBM and ICL mainframes; IBM AS/400 and System/38 business
minicomputers; Unix computers from
IBM, ICL, DEC, Hewlett-Packard and Sequent; IBM-type personal computers.
Price: not declared.
Sales and support: direct by Peterborough Software.
Customers: Unipay over 170, Unipersonnel over 70, Uni 2000 78, Open Door 48,
PS 2000 1,600, all in the UK; outside the UK, Uni 2000 has nine sites and
Open Door five.
Various users' views:
Pros: 'the company is a market leader . . . a very helpful company; Unix
open systems policy is welcome; integration of products works well; good
price; personal computer product is very flexible.
Users of other products, interviewed by Software At Work, had no specific
reasons for rejecting Peterborough Software.
