FT  02 OCT 92 / Vauxhall extends car price reductions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
VAUXHALL is extending its campaign to reduce car list prices with cuts of up
to Pounds 1,188 on its Cavalier, Calibra and Senator ranges, Kevin Done
writes.
At the same time, it is reducing its dealer margins from 17.5 per cent to 10
per cent - so customers are unlikely to see any cut in prices.
The move reduces the scope for discounting by dealers. Vauxhall claimed that
the parallel reductions in list prices and dealer margins had reduced 'the
haggle factor disliked by customers'.
